    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="ISA 28:1" />
    <char style="w" strong="H1945">Woe</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H5850">crown</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1348">pride</char>, to the <char style="w" strong="H7910">drunkards</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0669">Ephraim</char>, whose <char style="w" strong="H6643">glorious</char> <char style="w" strong="H8597">beauty</char> <char style="add">is</char> a <char style="w" strong="H5034">fading</char> <char style="w" strong="H6731">flower</char>, which <char style="add">are</char> on the <char style="w" strong="H7218">head</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H8081">fat</char> <char style="w" strong="H1516">valleys</char> of them that are <char style="w" strong="H1986">overcome</char> with <char style="w" strong="H3196">wine</char>!<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">28.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">overcome: Heb. broken</char></note> <verse eid="ISA 28:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ISA 28:2" />Behold, the <char style="w" strong="H0136">Lord</char> hath a <char style="w" strong="H2389">mighty</char> and strong <char style="w" strong="H0533">one</char>, <char style="add">which</char> as a <char style="w" strong="H2230">tempest</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1259">hail</char> <char style="add">and</char> a <char style="w" strong="H6986">destroying</char> <char style="w" strong="H8178">storm</char>, as a <char style="w" strong="H2230">flood</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3524">mighty</char> <char style="w" strong="H4325">waters</char> <char style="w" strong="H7857">overflowing</char>, shall cast <char style="w" strong="H3240">down</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char> with the <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char>. <verse eid="ISA 28:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ISA 28:3" />The <char style="w" strong="H5850">crown</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1348">pride</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H7910">drunkards</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0669">Ephraim</char>,