  <para style="p">
    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="ISA 29:13" />¶ Wherefore the <char style="w" strong="H0136">Lord</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3282">Forasmuch</char> as this <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> draw <char style="w" strong="H5066">near</char> <char style="add">me</char> with their <char style="w" strong="H6310">mouth</char>, and with their <char style="w" strong="H8193">lips</char> do <char style="w" strong="H3513">honour</char> me, but have <char style="w" strong="H7368">removed</char> their <char style="w" strong="H3820">heart</char> <char style="w" strong="H7368">far</char> from me, and their <char style="w" strong="H3374">fear</char> toward me is <char style="w" strong="H3925">taught</char> by the <char style="w" strong="H4687">precept</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0582">men</char>: <verse eid="ISA 29:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="ISA 29:14" />Therefore, behold, I will <char style="w" strong="H3254">proceed</char> to do a marvellous <char style="w" strong="H6381">work</char> among this <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>, <char style="add">even</char> a marvellous <char style="w" strong="H6381">work</char> and a <char style="w" strong="H6382">wonder</char>: for the <char style="w" strong="H2451">wisdom</char> of their <char style="w" strong="H2450">wise</char> <char style="add">men</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H0006">perish</char>, and the <char style="w" strong="H0998">understanding</char> of their <char style="w" strong="H0995">prudent</char> <char style="add">men</char> shall be <char style="w" strong="H5641">hid</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">29.14 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">proceed: Heb. add</char></note> <verse eid="ISA 29:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="ISA 29:15" /><char style="w" strong="H1945">Woe</char> unto them that seek <char style="w" strong="H6009">deep</char> to <char style="w" strong="H5641">hide</ch