    <char style="w" strong="H1945">Woe</char> to thee that <char style="w" strong="H7703">spoilest</char>, and thou <char style="add">wast</char> not <char style="w" strong="H7703">spoiled</char>; and dealest <char style="w" strong="H0898">treacherously</char>, and they dealt not <char style="w" strong="H0898">treacherously</char> with thee! when thou shalt <char style="w" strong="H8552">cease</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7703">spoil</char>, thou shalt be <char style="w" strong="H7703">spoiled</char>; <char style="add">and</char> when thou shalt make an <char style="w" strong="H5239">end</char> to deal <char style="w" strong="H0898">treacherously</char>, they shall deal <char style="w" strong="H0898">treacherously</char> with thee. <verse eid="ISA 33:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="ISA 33:2" />O <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, be <char style="w" strong="H2603">gracious</char> unto us; we have <char style="w" strong="H6960">waited</char> for thee: be thou their <char style="w" strong="H2220">arm</char> every <char style="w" strong="H1242">morning</char>, our <char style="w" strong="H3444">salvation</char> also in the <char style="w" strong="H6256">time</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6869">trouble</char>. <verse eid="ISA 33:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="ISA 33:3" />At the <char style="w" strong="H6963">noise</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1995">tumult</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H5074">fled</char>; at the lifting <char style="w" strong="H7427">up</char> of thyself the <char style="w" strong="H1471">nations</char> were <char style="w" strong="H5310">scattered</char>. <verse eid="ISA 33:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="ISA 33:4" />And your <char style="w" strong="H7998">spoil</char> shall be <char style="w" strong="H0622">gathered</char> <char style="add">like</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0625">gathering</char> of the <char style="w" strong