d="false">that…: Heb. of far distances</char></note> <verse eid="ISA 33:17" /><verse number="18" style="v" sid="ISA 33:18" />Thine <char style="w" strong="H3820">heart</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H1897">meditate</char> <char style="w" strong="H0367">terror</char>. Where <char style="add">is</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5608">scribe</char>? where <char style="add">is</char> the <char style="w" strong="H8254">receiver</char>? where <char style="add">is</char> he that <char style="w" strong="H5608">counted</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4026">towers</char>?<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">33.18 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">receiver: Heb. weigher?</char></note> <verse eid="ISA 33:18" /><verse number="19" style="v" sid="ISA 33:19" />Thou shalt not <char style="w" strong="H7200">see</char> a <char style="w" strong="H3267">fierce</char> <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>, a <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> of a <char style="w" strong="H6012">deeper</char> <char style="w" strong="H8193">speech</char> than thou canst <char style="w" strong="H8085">perceive</char>; of a <char style="w" strong="H3932">stammering</char> <char style="w" strong="H3956">tongue</char>, <char style="add">that thou canst</char> not <char style="w" strong="H0998">understand</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">33.19 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">stammering: or, ridiculous</char></note> <verse eid="ISA 33:19" /><verse number="20" style="v" sid="ISA 33:20" /><char style="w" strong="H2372">Look</char> upon <char style="w" strong="H6726">Zion</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H7151">city</char> of our <char style="w" strong="H4150">solemnities</char>: thine <char style="w" strong="H5869">eyes</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H7200">see</char> <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char> a <char style="w" strong="H7600">quiet</char> <char style="w" strong="H5116">habitation</char>, 