  <para style="p">
    <verse number="21" style="v" sid="ISA 44:21" />¶ <char style="w" strong="H2142">Remember</char> these, O <char style="w" strong="H3290">Jacob</char> and <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; for thou <char style="add">art</char> my <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char>: I have <char style="w" strong="H3335">formed</char> thee; thou <char style="add">art</char> my <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char>: O <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>, thou shalt not be <char style="w" strong="H5382">forgotten</char> of me. <verse eid="ISA 44:21" /><verse number="22" style="v" sid="ISA 44:22" />I have blotted <char style="w" strong="H4229">out</char>, as a thick <char style="w" strong="H5645">cloud</char>, thy <char style="w" strong="H6588">transgressions</char>, and, as a <char style="w" strong="H6051">cloud</char>, thy <char style="w" strong="H2403">sins</char>: <char style="w" strong="H7725">return</char> unto me; for I have <char style="w" strong="H1350">redeemed</char> thee. <verse eid="ISA 44:22" /><verse number="23" style="v" sid="ISA 44:23" /><char style="w" strong="H7442">Sing</char>, O ye <char style="w" strong="H8064">heavens</char>; for the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> hath <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> <char style="add">it:</char> <char style="w" strong="H7321">shout</char>, ye lower <char style="w" strong="H8482">parts</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char>: break <char style="w" strong="H6476">forth</char> into <char style="w" strong="H7440">singing</char>, ye <char style="w" strong="H2022">mountains</char>, O <char style="w" strong="H3293">forest</char>, and every <char style="w" strong="H6086">tree</char> therein: for the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> hath <char style="w" strong="H1350">redeemed</char> <char style="w" strong="H3290">Jacob</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6286">glorified</char> himself in <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>. <verse eid="ISA 44:23" /><verse number="24" style="v" sid="ISA 44:24" />Thus <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, thy <char style="w" strong="H1350">redeemer</char>, and he that <char style="w" strong="H3335">formed</char> thee from the <char style="w" strong="H0990">womb</char>, I <char style="add">am</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> that <char style="w" strong="H6213">maketh</char> all <char style="add">things;</char> that stretcheth <char style="w" strong="H5186">forth</char> the <char style="w" strong="H8064">heavens</char> alone; that spreadeth <char style="w" strong="H7554">abroad</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char> by myself; <verse eid="ISA 44:24" /><verse number="25" style="v" sid="ISA 44:25" />That <char style="w" strong="H6565">frustrateth</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0226">tokens</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H0907">liars</char>, and maketh <char style="w" strong="H7080">diviners</char> <char style="w" strong="H1984">mad</char>; that <char style="w" strong="H7725">turneth</char> <char style="w" strong="H2450">wise</char> <char style="add">men</char> <char style="w" strong="H0268">backward</char>, and maketh their <char style="w" strong="H1847">knowledge</char> <char style="w" strong="H5528">foolish</char>; <verse eid="ISA 44:25" /><verse number="26" style="v" sid="ISA 44:26" />That <char style="w" strong="H6965">confirmeth</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1697">word</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H7999">performeth</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6098">counsel</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H4397">messengers</char>; that <char style="w" strong="H0559">saith</char> to <char style="w" strong="H3389">Jerusalem</char>, Thou shalt be <char style="w" strong="H3427">inhabited</char>; and to the <char st