    <verse number="4" style="v" sid="ISA 51:4" />¶ <char style="w" strong="H7181">Hearken</char> unto me, my <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>; and give <char style="w" strong="H0238">ear</char> unto me, O my <char style="w" strong="H3816">nation</char>: for a <char style="w" strong="H8451">law</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H3318">proceed</char> from me, and I will make my <char style="w" strong="H4941">judgment</char> to <char style="w" strong="H7280">rest</char> for a <char style="w" strong="H0216">light</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>. <verse eid="ISA 51:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="ISA 51:5" />My <char style="w" strong="H6664">righteousness</char> <char style="add">is</char> <char style="w" strong="H7138">near</char>; my <char style="w" strong="H3468">salvation</char> is gone <char style="w" strong="H3318">forth</char>, and mine <char style="w" strong="H2220">arms</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H8199">judge</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>; the <char style="w" strong="H0339">isles</char> shall <char style="w" strong="H6960">wait</char> upon me, and on mine <char style="w" strong="H2220">arm</char> shall they <char style="w" strong="H3176">trust</char>. <verse eid="ISA 51:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="ISA 51:6" />Lift <char style="w" strong="H5375">up</char> your <char style="w" strong="H5869">eyes</char> to the <char style="w" strong="H8064">heavens</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5027">look</char> upon the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char> beneath: for the <char style="w" strong="H8064">heavens</char> shall vanish <char style="w" strong="H4414">away</char> like <char style="w" strong="H6227">smoke</char>, and the <char style="w" strong="H0776">earth</char> shall wax <char style="w" strong="H1086">old</char> like a <char style="w" strong="H0899">garment</char>, and they that <char style="w" strong="H3427">dwell</char> therein shall <char style="w" strong="H4